{
  "stem": "24885.2",
  "chunk_idx": 10,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 4.8,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "And my sister-- my brother-in-law worked in the ammunition factory, and he saw what was going on, that they were going to be shipped out too, he came back and thought he can go over with his wife and child.",
      "word_count": 40
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] At this point, we already lived with the Wehrmacht.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Myself and my brother, one brother.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "The other brother was in the ammunition factory.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "The youngest one.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "William.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "No, Morris was with me.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "He was in the ammunition factory.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Then two weeks later, they did the second liquidation that they liquidate the ghetto from-- from 30,000 people down to 5,0000 or 2,000, you know, I don't-- and they made it very small.",
      "word_count": 33
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And this was all people that they needed, craftsman or whatever it was.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Then one day I was going out.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I had the advantage of being with the horse-- I could go any place I wanted to, because the horse was my passport.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "One day I came down, I had to go to shoe the horse.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And I came down, I stopped off at the small ghetto and the captain there, the-- whoever he was-- says to me, I wonder who is free to go alone, you or the horse?",
      "word_count": 34
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 35,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I couldn't go alone.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 35,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "It's the horse that was free to go.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 35,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "I was with the horse, I was safe.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 35,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Alone, I would have been shot.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 35,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "That's the way life was for a while.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 35,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "Then one morning we were right near a railroad track, because there was another group of Jewish people who worked on a loading barrels of oil or gas.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 35,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "It was a station there right next to ours-- depot, or whatever it was.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 35,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And I saw a train stopped, and for some reason it was a hot day and was Kippur day.",
      "word_count": 19
    }
  ],
